# ============================================================
# IDENTITY CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: identity
scope: identity.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for identity.

## policy_rules
Identity policy constrains:
- who may view which identity detail
- who may alter identity-linked state
- how canonical and projected identity may be disclosed
- when identity paths must be denied or escalated

## required_behavior
- identity disclosure scope must be explicit
- alteration scope must be explicit
- canonical/projection split must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- public identity summary
- holder-scoped detail
- operator/reviewer detail
- historical identity detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow identity-linked action only for valid scope
- allow disclosure only for allowed actors
- deny hidden identity substitution
- deny disclosure beyond allowed scope

## escalation_rules
If identity basis,
alteration scope,
canonical/projection mode,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the identity path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- disclosure policy is explicit
- canonical/projection policy is explicit
- denial behavior is explicit
- escalation rules are explicit
